  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 2 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 13 high, 8 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD); plus 10 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Modlin (WMI/EPMO). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: low‑visibility takeoff restrictions, RVR limitations and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Tromsø Airport, Langnes (TOS/ENTC), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) and 9 others.",
